Abstract. Provide an abstract of no more than 250 words on page 2 of the
manuscript. Abstracts should explain to the general reader the major
contributions of the article. References in the abstract must be cited in
full within the abstract itself and cited in the text.  Significance
Statement. Authors must submit a 120-wordmaximum statement about the
significance of their research paper written at a level understandable to an
undergraduateeducated scientist outside their field of specialty. The primary
goal of the Significance Statement is to explain the relevance of the work in
broad context to a broad readership. The Significance Statement appears in
the paper itself and is required for all research papers.
